com.impinj.octane

Enum SearchMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SearchMode>
      • com.impinj.octane.SearchMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SearchMode>

    public enum SearchMode
extends java.lang.Enum<SearchMode>
    This enumeration describes the method the reader uses to search for tags. Gen2 provides rudimentary building blocks to inventory populations of tags The Impinj reader creates high level inventory search modes from these gen2 operations.
    See Also:
    Gen2 Standard page 51 section 6.3.22

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DualTarget
      The reader alternates between A to B and B to A inventory.
      ReaderSelected
      The reader selects the best inventory search mode for the chosen session
      SingleTarget
      The reader performs repeated inventory from A to B.
      TagFocus
      The reader uses Impinj Tag Focus to provide a single target inventory in session 1 with a very short persistence time.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ReaderSelected

        public static final SearchMode ReaderSelected
        The reader selects the best inventory search mode for the chosen session

      • SingleTarget

        public static final SearchMode SingleTarget
        The reader performs repeated inventory from A to B. Each tag will be inventory only once until it session persistence decays according to the specification

      • DualTarget

        public static final SearchMode DualTarget
        The reader alternates between A to B and B to A inventory. Each tag will be reported each time is switches back and forth between states.

      • TagFocus

        public static final SearchMode TagFocus
        The reader uses Impinj Tag Focus to provide a single target inventory in session 1 with a very short persistence time.
